---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const lastUpdated = 'March 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How DevRel(ish) collects, uses, and protects your personal information."
>
  <section class="policy-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow">◎ Plain language, we promise</div>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p>
        We've written this to be readable, not to bury the important stuff in
        legalese. Last updated: <strong>{lastUpdated}</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="policy-body">
    <div class="container policy-layout">
      <nav class="policy-toc" aria-label="Table of contents">
        <p class="toc-heading">On this page</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="#what-we-collect">What we collect</a></li>
          <li><a href="#how-we-use-it">How we use it</a></li>
          <li><a href="#who-sees-it">Who sees it</a></li>
          <li><a href="#organizer-rules">Organizer rules</a></li>
          <li><a href="#retention">Data retention</a></li>
          <li><a href="#your-rights">Your rights</a></li>
          <li><a href="#contact">Contact us</a></li>
        </ul>
      </nav>

      <div class="policy-content">
        <section id="what-we-collect" class="policy-section">
          <h2>What we collect</h2>

          <h3>When you RSVP to a gathering</h3>
          <p>We ask for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Name</strong> — so the organizer knows who's coming</li>
            <li>
              <strong>Email address</strong> — so the organizer can reach you about
              the event
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Job title</strong> — to help the group understand who's attending
            </li>
            <li><strong>Company</strong> — same reason</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We do not require an account to RSVP. We do not collect payment
            information. We do not use tracking cookies or analytics on RSVP
            submissions.
          </p>

          <h3>When you apply to start a group</h3>
          <p>
            We collect your name (via account creation after approval), email
            address, and the details of your proposed group. This is used to
            review your application and, if approved, to give you access to
            manage your group.
          </p>

          <h3>When you create an account (group organizers only)</h3>
          <p>
            Attendees do not need accounts. Group organizers create an account
            with their name and email address. We store a hashed password — we
            never store your password in plain text and we cannot recover it.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="how-we-use-it" class="policy-section">
          <h2>How we use it</h2>
          <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Manage RSVPs and track event capacity</li>
            <li>
              Allow group organizers to know who is attending their events
            </li>
            <li>
              Send you information about the specific event you RSVPed for (if
              the organizer chooses to contact attendees)
            </li>
            <li>Operate the DevRel(ish) platform</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We do <strong>not</strong> sell your data. We do not share it with advertisers.
            We do not use it for any purpose unrelated to organizing DevRel(ish) gatherings.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="who-sees-it" class="policy-section">
          <h2>Who sees your information</h2>

          <h3>Group organizers</h3>
          <p>
            The organizer of the gathering you RSVP for can see your name,
            email, job title, and company. They can download this list in order
            to manage attendance and communicate with attendees. See <a
              href="#organizer-rules">Organizer rules</a
            >
            below for how they're permitted to use it.
          </p>

          <h3>DevRel(ish) administrators</h3>
          <p>
            Site administrators can access RSVP data for the purpose of
            operating and moderating the platform.
          </p>

          <h3>No one else</h3>
          <p>
            We don't share your personal information with any third-party
            services, data brokers, sponsors, or other organizations.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          id="organizer-rules"
          class="policy-section policy-section-highlight"
        >
          <h2>Organizer rules for attendee data</h2>
          <p>
            Group organizers agree to the following when they apply to run a
            DevRel(ish) group. Violations may result in removal from the
            platform.
          </p>

          <h3>✓ Organizers may</h3>
          <ul class="rules-list rules-allowed">
            <li>
              Contact attendees about the specific event they RSVPed for —
              logistics, location changes, cancellations, and so on
            </li>
            <li>
              Add attendees to a mailing list for the group's future events,
              provided they provide an easy way to unsubscribe
            </li>
            <li>
              Share aggregate, anonymized information (e.g. "we had 40
              attendees, mostly developer advocates") without identifying
              individuals
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h3>✗ Organizers may not</h3>
          <ul class="rules-list rules-prohibited">
            <li>
              Use attendee contact information to market products, services, or
              anything unrelated to their DevRel(ish) group's events
            </li>
            <li>Send unsolicited bulk email (spam) of any kind</li>
            <li>
              Share, sell, or transfer the attendee list to any third party,
              including event sponsors, employers, or other organizations
            </li>
            <li>
              Retain attendee data beyond what is reasonably needed to operate
              the group
            </li>
            <li>
              Use the data for any purpose other than organizing in-person
              social events for their DevRel(ish) group
            </li>
          </ul>

          <p class="rules-note">
            If you believe an organizer has misused your contact information,
            please contact us at <a href="mailto:admin@devrelish.tech"
              >admin@devrelish.tech</a
            >
            and we will investigate and take action.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="retention" class="policy-section">
          <h2>Data retention</h2>
          <p>
            RSVP data is retained and accessible to the organizer for as long as
            the associated group remains active on the platform. Once the group
            is removed, the RSVP data is no longer accessible to the organizer.
          </p>
          <p>
            Group organizer accounts are retained until the organizer requests
            deletion or the group is removed from the platform.
          </p>
          <p>
            You can request deletion of your RSVP record at any time by emailing
            <a href="mailto:admin@devrelish.tech">admin@devrelish.tech</a> with the
            email address you used to RSVP.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="your-rights" class="policy-section">
          <h2>Your rights</h2>
          <p>Regardless of where you are in the world, you can:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Access</strong> the personal information we hold about you
            </li>
            <li><strong>Correct</strong> inaccurate information</li>
            <li><strong>Delete</strong> your RSVP records or account</li>
            <li>
              <strong>Object</strong> to a specific use of your data — for example,
              if an organizer is contacting you in a way that violates the rules above
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            To exercise any of these rights, email
            <a href="mailto:admin@devrelish.tech">admin@devrelish.tech</a>.
            We'll respond within 30 days.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you are in the European Economic Area or the UK, you also have
            the right to lodge a complaint with your local data protection
            authority.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="contact" class="policy-section">
          <h2>Contact us</h2>
          <p>
            Questions about this policy, requests to access or delete your data,
            or reports of organizer misuse should be sent to:
          </p>
          <p>
            <a href="mailto:admin@devrelish.tech">admin@devrelish.tech</a>
          </p>
          <p>
            We may update this policy from time to time. If we make material
            changes, we'll update the date at the top of this page.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .policy-hero {
    padding: 3rem 0 2rem;
    background: var(--color-surface-warm);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .eyebrow {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: var(--size-sm);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    background: rgba(232, 112, 74, 0.1);
    padding: 0.25rem 0.875rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-full);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .policy-hero h1 {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .policy-hero p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: var(--size-lg);
  }

  .policy-body {
    padding: 3rem 0 5rem;
  }

  .policy-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  /* Table of contents */
  .policy-toc {
    position: sticky;
    top: 88px;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 2px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .toc-heading {
    font-size: var(--size-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    max-width: none;
  }

  .policy-toc ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.375rem;
  }

  .policy-toc a {
    font-size: var(--size-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    display: block;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    transition:
      color var(--transition),
      background var(--transition);
  }

  .policy-toc a:hover {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    background: var(--color-surface-warm);
  }

  /* Content */
  .policy-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .policy-section {
    padding: 2rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--color-border);
  }

  .policy-section:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .policy-section h2 {
    font-size: var(--size-2xl);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .policy-section h3 {
    font-size: var(--size-base);
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .policy-section p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: var(--size-base);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    max-width: 68ch;
  }

  .policy-section ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    padding-left: 0;
  }

  .policy-section ul li {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: var(--size-base);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .policy-section ul li::before {
    content: '–';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  /* Highlight box for organizer rules */
  .policy-section-highlight {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 2px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    padding: 2rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border) !important;
  }

  .rules-list {
    padding-left: 0;
  }

  .rules-allowed li::before {
    content: '✓';
    color: var(--color-accent-dark);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .rules-prohibited li::before {
    content: '✗';
    color: #c0392b;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .rules-note {
    font-size: var(--size-sm) !important;
    background: var(--color-surface-warm);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    margin-top: 1rem !important;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .policy-layout {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .policy-toc {
      position: static;
    }
  }
</style>
